                    "comment": "pitrou commented on a change in pull request #1995: ARROW-2278: [Python] Fix incorrect numpy struct array serialization\nURL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/1995#discussion_r186388500\n \n \n\n ##########\n File path: python/pyarrow/serialization.py\n ##########\n @@ -30,27 +31,83 @@\n except ImportError:\n     cloudpickle = builtin_pickle\n \n+if six.PY2:\n+    JSONDecodeError = ValueError\n+else:\n+    JSONDecodeError = json.decoder.JSONDecodeError\n \n # ----------------------------------------------------------------------\n # Set up serialization for numpy with dtype object (primitive types are\n # handled efficiently with Arrow's Tensor facilities, see\n # python_to_arrow.cc)\n \n+\n+class DTypeJsonEncoder(json.JSONEncoder):\n+    @classmethod\n+    def object_converter(cls, data):\n+        if isinstance(data, tuple):\n+            return {\n+                '__tuple__': True,\n+                'data': tuple(cls.object_converter(e) for e in data)\n+            }\n+        elif isinstance(data, np.dtype):\n+            return {\n+                '__dtype__': True,\n+                'data': data.str\n+            }\n+        elif isinstance(data, list):\n+            return [\n+                cls.object_converter(e)\n+                for e in data\n+            ]\n+        elif isinstance(data, dict):\n+            return {\n+                key: cls.object_converter(value)\n+                for key, value in data.items()\n+            }\n+        else:\n+            return data\n+\n+    def encode(self, obj):\n+        return super(DTypeJsonEncoder, self).encode(self.object_converter(obj))\n+\n+\n+def _dtype_json_object_hook(obj):\n+    if '__tuple__' in obj:\n+        return tuple(obj['data'])\n+    elif '__dtype__' in obj:\n+        return np.dtype(obj['data'])\n+    else:\n+        return obj\n+\n+\n def _serialize_numpy_array_list(obj):\n     if obj.dtype.str != '|O':\n         # Make the array c_contiguous if necessary so that we can call change\n         # the view.\n         if not obj.flags.c_contiguous:\n             obj = np.ascontiguousarray(obj)\n-        return obj.view('uint8'), obj.dtype.str\n+\n+        if obj.dtype.fields is not None:\n+            dtype = DTypeJsonEncoder().encode(dict(obj.dtype.fields))\n \n Review comment:\n   I think it's overkill to bring json into this and customize the encoder. You could simply use pickle, which Numpy dtypes support natively (you could also use `dtype.descr`, but it won't work with all dtypes).\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------\nThis is an automated message from the Apache Git Service.\nTo respond to the message, please log on GitHub and use the\nURL above to go to the specific comment.\n \nFor queries about this service, please contact Infrastructure at:\nusers@infra.apache.org\n",
